What type of instruction should you search for within the ladder logic to see how the OTL instruction is turned off?

  • Search for the Examine if Closed (XIC) instruction
  • Search for the Unlatch Instruction
  • Search for the “Else” condition
  • You don’t need to search because the Coil will not turn off until the power is cycled off then on

Hints:

Question 3 - Answered by you 9 hours ago
2 points

What is the Bitwise Exclusive (XOR) of the following binary numbers? 00001101 multiplied by 10000101

Provide your answer including all eight bits including leading zeros if any.

Answer format: ########

Hints:

  1. A Binary number contains 8 value placeholders. Working left to right, the largest value represented is 128, followed by 64, 32, 16, 8, 4, 2 ,1

    Largest number represented by 11111111 is 255 in decimal.

  2. If you want to calculate manually, you evaluate each place.

  3. Googling an XOR calculator will help!

Objective: Level 3

Scenario Intel Report

In an unprecedented move of apparent retaliation against the industrial cybersecurity firm DRAGOS Inc, XENOTIME has breached the SOGARD Brewery industrial control range of DRAGOS. XENOTIME has been tracked by Dragos since 2017 when the Dragos Professional Services team discovered ICS-tailored malware deployed against at least one victim in the Middle East. The Dragos Intel team identifies this malware as Trisis because it targets Schneider Electric’s Triconex safety instrumented system (SIS), enabling the replacement of logic in final control elements.

Trisis has since been called the world’s deadliest malware and the first malware designed to kill humans. In February 2019, Dragos identified a change in Xenotime behavior: starting in late 2018, Xenotime began probing the networks of electric utility organizations in the U.S. and elsewhere using similar tactics to the group’s operations against oil and gas companies.

The SOGARD brewery appears to be the sole target of the XENOTIME activity group’s incursion. The intrusion was discovered when the latest batch of the SOGARD 15% abv dark stout, “Dragon Fire,” came out as a 4% abv ultra-light. DRAGOS believes that the formula for the SOGARD dark stout was also stolen during the intrusion.

The DRAGOS professional services team has identified a new ICS-tailored malware that was deployed on the SOGARD range. The DRAGOS Intel team has identified this malware as Beersis as it is engineered to target breweries.
